# PixSlay — Technical Implementation Guide

Read this file alongside CONTEXT.md, DESIGN.md, and SCREENS.md before writing any code.
This file captures every hard-won lesson from previous build attempts.
Follow every rule here exactly — these are not preferences, they are fixes for known failures.

---

## Stack

Single standalone HTML file. Vanilla HTML + CSS + JavaScript only.
No frameworks. No build tools. No npm. No React. No Vue.
Google Fonts CDN import in `<head>` for Plus Jakarta Sans.
No other external dependencies.
Must work by double-clicking in a browser or dropping on Netlify.
Must fill the screen on a real mobile phone like a native app.

---

## File Structure

One file: `index.html`

Inside the `<script>` tag, organise code in this order:
1. Design tokens object
2. State object + go() function
3. Utility functions (toast, popup, icon, logo)
4. Shared component functions (sbar, tbar, navbar, switchPill, floatInput, otpRow, buttons, faceChip, filterBar, actionTabs, photoCell, photoGrid, bottomSheet, eventCard, photoIllustration)
5. Screen functions (one function per screen, named screenVarunReg, screenVarunOTP, etc.)
6. SCREEN_MAP object (maps screen name strings to screen functions)
7. render() function
8. postRender() function (animations, timers, event listeners added after DOM insert)
9. Initial render call

