## Global CSS Classes

Two reusable utility classes are defined in `<style>` and used throughout:

### `.hscroll` — horizontal scroll rows
Hides the scrollbar on any horizontally-scrolling container (people row, category pills, tabs, contact chips, etc.).
```css
.hscroll { -ms-overflow-style:none; scrollbar-width:none; }
.hscroll::-webkit-scrollbar { display:none; }
```

### `.pscroll` — primary photo browsing scroll containers
**Design rule:** Primary photo browsing experiences should use visually hidden scrollbars for a cleaner and more immersive experience.

Applies to: `#tagging-grid` (My Photos / Group / Saved / Downloaded tabs), and any future immersive photo grid container.
Momentum scrolling is preserved via `-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch`.
Scrollability is communicated naturally through partially-visible content, continuous grid flow, and touch interaction — not by a visible scrollbar rail.
```css
.pscroll { -ms-overflow-style:none; scrollbar-width:none;
           -webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch; }
.pscroll::-webkit-scrollbar { display:none; }
```

Do **not** apply `.pscroll` to form/content screens (registration, profile, OTP, home, sync). Those are not immersive browsing experiences.

