## Floating Label Inputs — CRITICAL, DO NOT USE CSS SELECTORS

### Why CSS fails here
CSS `~` sibling selectors (`.fi:focus ~ .fi-lbl`) do not reliably trigger
on HTML that is injected via innerHTML or template literals in all browsers.
The label either never floats or only floats after a page reload.

### The correct approach — inline JS only

Every input uses direct `style` manipulation via `onfocus` and `onblur`.
The label position is also set correctly at render time based on whether the field has a value.

```javascript
function floatInput(label, id, value='', type='text') {
  const filled = value.length > 0;

  const FLOATED = `top:0;transform:translateY(-50%);font-size:11px;font-weight:600;padding:0 4px;`;
  const RESTING = `top:50%;transform:translateY(-50%);font-size:14px;font-weight:400;padding:0;`;

  // Set initial label style based on whether field is pre-filled
  const initLblStyle = filled
    ? `position:absolute;left:14px;background:#fff;pointer-events:none;transition:all .15s;${FLOATED}color:${T.textT};`
    : `position:absolute;left:14px;background:#fff;pointer-events:none;transition:all .15s;${RESTING}color:${T.textT};`;

  const initBorder = filled ? `0.5px solid ${T.blueBdr}` : `0.5px solid ${T.bgSub}`;

  return `
    <div style="position:relative;margin-bottom:12px;">
      <input
        id="${id}"
        type="${type}"
        value="${value}"
        autocomplete="off"
        style="width:100%;height:52px;border:${initBorder};border-radius:10px;
               padding:20px 14px 7px;font-family:inherit;font-size:14px;
               font-weight:400;color:${T.text};background:#fff;outline:none;
               transition:border .15s;"
        onfocus="
          var l=document.getElementById('${id}-lbl');
          if(l) l.style.cssText='position:absolute;left:14px;background:#fff;pointer-events:none;transition:all .15s;${FLOATED}color:${T.blue};';
          this.style.border='1px solid ${T.blue}';"
        onblur="
          var l=document.getElementById('${id}-lbl');
          if(this.value) {
            if(l) l.style.cssText='position:absolute;left:14px;background:#fff;pointer-events:none;transition:all .15s;${FLOATED}color:${T.textT};';
            this.style.border='0.5px solid ${T.blueBdr}';
          } else {
            if(l) l.style.cssText='position:absolute;left:14px;background:#fff;pointer-events:none;transition:all .15s;${RESTING}color:${T.textT};';
            this.style.border='0.5px solid ${T.bgSub}';
          }"
      >
      <label
        id="${id}-lbl"
        for="${id}"
        style="${initLblStyle}"
      >${label}</label>
    </div>`;
}
```

### Test this before moving on
After rendering any screen with a floatInput:
- Tap an empty field → label must immediately float to top
- Type something → label stays at top, border turns blue
- Tab away (blur) → label stays at top, border turns to light blue
- Render a pre-filled field → label must already be at top on first paint, no jump

