## OTP Input — CRITICAL, DO NOT USE A HIDDEN SINGLE INPUT

### Why a hidden input fails
A single opacity:0 input of 1px×1px cannot receive touch events reliably on iOS Safari.
`element.focus()` called programmatically without a direct user gesture is silently ignored by iOS.
The visual boxes on top block the hidden input from receiving taps.

### The correct approach — 6 real inputs

```javascript
function otpRow(id, dest) {
  const boxes = Array.from({length:6}, (_,i) => `
    <input
      type="tel"
      inputmode="numeric"
      maxlength="1"
      id="${id}-${i}"
      style="width:40px;height:52px;border:0.5px solid ${T.bgSub};border-radius:10px;
             background:#fff;font-size:24px;font-weight:800;color:${T.blue};
             text-align:center;font-family:inherit;outline:none;
             transition:border .1s, background .1s;"
      onfocus="this.style.border='1.5px solid ${T.blue}'; this.select();"
      onblur="this.style.border=this.value?'0.5px solid ${T.blueBdr}':'0.5px solid ${T.bgSub}';"
      oninput="otpInput('${id}',${i},'${dest}',this)"
      onkeydown="otpBack('${id}',${i},event)"
    />`).join('');

  return `<div style="display:flex;gap:8px;justify-content:center;">${boxes}</div>`;
}

function otpInput(id, i, dest, el) {
  // Strip non-digits, keep only last character
  el.value = el.value.replace(/[^0-9]/g,'').slice(-1);
  if (el.value) {
    el.style.background = T.blueTint;
    el.style.border = `0.5px solid ${T.blueBdr}`;
    const next = document.getElementById(`${id}-${i+1}`);
    if (next) {
      next.focus();
    } else {
      // All 6 filled — navigate after brief pause
      setTimeout(() => go(dest), 300);
    }
  }
}

function otpBack(id, i, e) {
  if (e.key === 'Backspace') {
    const el = document.getElementById(`${id}-${i}`);
    if (!el.value && i > 0) {
      const prev = document.getElementById(`${id}-${i-1}`);
      if (prev) {
        prev.value = '';
        prev.style.background = '#fff';
        prev.style.border = `0.5px solid ${T.bgSub}`;
        prev.focus();
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Auto-focus first box after render
In postRender(), after the OTP screen is in the DOM:
```javascript
// Focus first OTP box after DOM is painted
setTimeout(() => {
  const first = document.getElementById(`${id}-0`);
  if (first) first.focus();
}, 150);
```

### Test this before moving on
- Tap box 1 → keyboard opens, cursor visible inside box
- Type a digit → digit shows, cursor jumps to box 2
- Type 6 digits in sequence → auto-navigates to next screen
- Tap box 3 → cursor lands in box 3
- Press backspace on empty box → cursor jumps to previous box

