## Bottom Sheets — CRITICAL, DO NOT BLOCK BUTTON TAPS

### Why buttons inside sheets stop working
If the overlay div covers the entire screen AND has `pointer-events:auto`,
taps on buttons inside the sheet card bubble up to the overlay and either
close the sheet or get swallowed before reaching the button.

### The correct approach — stopPropagation on the card

```html
<!-- The overlay closes the sheet when tapped -->
<div
  id="${id}-overlay"
  onclick="closeSheet('${id}')"
  style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:rgba(0,0,0,.45);z-index:200;
         display:flex;align-items:flex-end;"
>
  <!-- The card stops tap propagation so buttons inside work -->
  <div
    onclick="event.stopPropagation()"
    style="width:100%;background:#fff;border-radius:20px 20px 0 0;
           padding-bottom:24px;z-index:201;"
  >
    <div style="width:40px;height:4px;background:${T.bgSub};border-radius:2px;margin:8px auto 0;"></div>
    <!-- Sheet content here — all buttons fully tappable -->
  </div>
</div>
```

### Opening and closing sheets
```javascript
function openSheet(id) {
  const el = document.getElementById(id + '-overlay');
  if (el) el.style.display = 'flex';
}
function closeSheet(id) {
  const el = document.getElementById(id + '-overlay');
  if (el) el.style.display = 'none';
}
```

### Test every sheet before moving on
Open each sheet. Tap every single button inside it.
Confirm each button responds — navigates, shows toast, or triggers an action.
If any button is unresponsive, the stopPropagation is missing or z-index is wrong.

