## Screen Layout Pattern

Every screen is an absolutely positioned div filling the phone container.
Only one screen is visible at a time.

```javascript
function render() {
  const phone = document.getElementById('phone');
  // Remove previous screen
  const old = phone.querySelector('.screen');
  if (old) old.remove();

  // Build and insert new screen
  const fn = SCREEN_MAP[state.screen];
  if (!fn) { state.screen = 'entry'; render(); return; }

  const tmp = document.createElement('div');
  tmp.innerHTML = fn();
  const screen = tmp.firstElementChild;
  phone.appendChild(screen);

  // Run post-render hooks (animations, timers, event listeners)
  postRender();
}
```

Each screen function returns a string of HTML. The outermost element must be:
```html
<div class="screen" style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background:#F8F7F5;">
```

