`taggingSetCategory(cat)` maps the pill name → scene key → dims non-matching photos to opacity 0.12.

### People row (circular avatars)
- 4 circular avatars: VR (You — identified), MA/KA/unk (Unknown — unidentified)
- Each: 56px circle, colored gradient bg, colored ring (solid=identified, dashed=unidentified)
- Name label below (11px), photo count in brackets (10px)
- Tap identified → `taggingSetFace(face)` toggles filter + dims other photos to 0.15
- Tap unidentified → `taggingIdentifyPerson(personId)` → `showIdentifySheet(personId, count, avatarBg)`
- Identify sheet: "Is this you?" headline, person's saturated gradient avatar (72px), name chips (Varun/Mayank/Kavitha/Beulah/Vishal), no text input. Tap chip → `identifyPickName` highlights it + enables Confirm. "Not sure" dismisses.
- After `confirmIdentify`: `identifySelectedName` is read, avatar updates to identified state, ring becomes solid, tap re-wired to `taggingSetFace`. Fires once per person.
