## Moment A — Identify Yourself Sheet

Auto-triggers 1.2 seconds after varun-event first renders (and kavitha-event after sync completes).
Only triggers if `state.identifiedFaces.length === 0`.

Sheet contains:
- Headline: "Which one is you?" 20px 800
- Sub: "Tap your face so we know who you are." 13px secondary colour
- 3×2 grid of face tiles (coloured squares with initials — simulates cropped face photos)
- "That's me" primary button — DISABLED until a face tile is tapped
- "Skip for now" ghost button — same height and width as primary, always enabled

On face tile tap: tile gets blue border + checkmark badge. "That's me" button activates.
On "That's me": close sheet, show toast "You're identified!", trigger Moment B after 2s.
On "Skip": close sheet, trigger Moment B after 2s if unidentified faces remain.

