## Moment B — Identify Others Sheet

Partial height sheet (~65% screen). Appears for each unidentified face chip in turn.
Shows one face at a time. Never more than one.

Sheet contains:
- 80px circle showing a coloured placeholder (simulates cropped face)
- "This person appears in X of your photos." 13px secondary
- Name input field (use inline JS floated label pattern from above)
- Suggestion chips row: Beulah / Kavitha / Mayank / Vishal / Anand
  Each chip is a real `<button>` that on tap fills the name input AND floats its label
- "Confirm" primary button — disabled until name input has content
- "Skip" ghost button — same height, always enabled

On suggestion chip tap:
```javascript
function fillMomBName(name) {
  const inp = document.getElementById('momB-input');
  const lbl = document.getElementById('momB-input-lbl');
  if (!inp) return;
  inp.value = name;
  inp.style.border = `0.5px solid ${T.blueBdr}`;
  if (lbl) lbl.style.cssText = `position:absolute;left:14px;background:#fff;
    pointer-events:none;top:0;transform:translateY(-50%);font-size:11px;
    font-weight:600;color:${T.textT};padding:0 4px;`;
  // Enable confirm button
  const btn = document.getElementById('momB-confirm');
  if (btn) btn.disabled = false;
}
```

On Confirm: save to `state.identifiedFaces`, close sheet, show toast "[name] identified!",
after 1s show next unidentified face sheet. When all done: dismiss permanently.
On Skip: mark as skipped in state, move to next face.

