## Photo Sync Screen (varun-sync)

### Flow order — screen → sheet → sync
1. `screenVarunSync()` renders: informational card (State A copy), no inline CTAs.
   Sticky bottom: "Set up trip photos" (blue) + "I'll do this later" (ghost).
2. "Set up trip photos" → `showSyncReassuranceSheet()` opens the sheet.
3. Sheet: "When should we look for trip photos?" — 4 pre-filled fields, "Allow access & continue" / "Cancel".
4. "Allow access & continue" → `closeSyncReassuranceSheet(true)`:
   — saves field values to state.syncTiming
   — calls `syncUpdateCardToRunning()` (swaps card to State B/C copy)
   — calls `syncSetStickyState('syncing')` (primary becomes "View my photos" disabled)
   — calls `syncStartPhase1()`
5. "Cancel" or overlay tap → `closeSyncReassuranceSheet(false)` → no save, no sync.

### Card content swap — syncUpdateCardToRunning()
Updates these IDs in-place (no re-render):
  sync-card-title  → "You're all set for Karjat."
  sync-card-sub    → "Just enjoy the trip and keep clicking photos."
  sync-card-window → display:none (trip window line hidden)
  sync-card-status → display:block, text = "Looking from [fromDate], [fromTime] to [toDate], [toTime]"

### Sticky bottom area — dynamic state swap (no re-render)
```javascript
syncSetStickyState('syncing')  // "View my photos" disabled, grey
syncSetStickyState('done')     // "View my photos" active, blue, onclick → varun-tagging
```
Both target id="sync-primary-btn" and update textContent, disabled, style, onclick in-place.
Called from: closeSyncReassuranceSheet(true) → 'syncing'; syncComplete() → 'done'.
"I'll do this later" ghost is always static — always goes to varun-home.

### Reassurance sheet
```javascript
showSyncReassuranceSheet()          // appends overlay, slides sheet up, focuses sr-from-time
closeSyncReassuranceSheet(bool)     // saves timing if bool=true, slides sheet down, starts or cancels
```
Sheet always shows all 4 fields (no expand mechanic). Fields: sr-from-date, sr-from-time,
sr-to-date, sr-to-time — all floatInput, type="text", inputmode="text".
Auto-focus: sr-from-time (users mainly adjust time, not date).
Helper text: "We'll only use this to find photos from the trip." 11px #A8A49F centered.

### Saving edited values
closeSyncReassuranceSheet(true) reads all 4 field values and writes non-empty ones to
state.syncTiming before closing. state.syncTiming is the single source of truth —
the sync card subtext reads from it on render.

### Progress animation
- Phase 1: syncStartPhase1() — counter shows "Scanning N photos..." from first tick
- At 60%: amber banner, 1s pause, then syncStartPhase2()
- At 100%: syncComplete():
  — hides sync-card-status (trip window line moves into results section, no duplication)
  — fades progress section out (300ms), then fades results in
  — calls syncSetStickyState('done')

### Results section layout (sync-results div)
Rendered at screen build time, hidden (display:none, opacity:0) until syncComplete().
Contains in order:
  1. Two-stat flex row: "34 Trip photos" | "2 Trip videos" — 28px 800 numbers, vertical divider
  2. Contextual trip window line — 11px #A8A49F, reads state.syncTiming at render time
  3. Photo preview strip — 5 flex children with flex:1, aspect-ratio:1, border-radius:10px
     Four gradient thumbnails (scene colours) + "+27" overflow pill (#F0EEEB bg)
     Not interactive — static decoration only
  4. Privacy line — 12px #A8A49F centered

### Progress animation
- Phase 1: `syncStartPhase1()` — setInterval every 25ms, +1.0 per tick, 0→60%
  - At 60%: show amber banner, pause 1s, then call `syncStartPhase2()`
- Phase 2: `syncStartPhase2()` — setInterval every 37ms, +1.0 per tick, 60→100%
  - At 100%: call `syncComplete()`
- `syncComplete()`: sets syncDone=true, fades out progress section, fades in results row,
  activates "View my photos" button.

### Globals — reset in postRender on every visit
```javascript
var syncPhaseInt = null;
var syncProg     = 0;
var syncDone     = false;
// postRender resets these so re-entering the screen always starts clean
```

### "View my photos" and "I'll do this later"
- "View my photos": disabled (background bgSub, text textT) until syncDone===true.
  On complete: background=blue, color=white, cursor=pointer.
- "I'll do this later": always active ghost button, same height (44px) as any adjacent secondary.
  Never greyed or hidden — the app does not guilt-trip users.

