## Transitions and Animations — Minimal, Modern

All transitions use CSS only. No JS animation libraries. No external dependencies.
Duration: 280ms for screens and sheets. 200ms for components. Easing: cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1) throughout — this is Material Design standard easing, feels native on both iOS and Android.
Never animate layout properties (width, height, padding, margin) — only transform and opacity.

### Screen transitions — slide in from right, slide out to left
```css
@keyframes slideIn  { from { transform:translateX(100%); opacity:0; } to { transform:translateX(0); opacity:1; } }
@keyframes slideOut { from { transform:translateX(0); opacity:1; } to { transform:translateX(-8%); opacity:0; } }
.screen-enter { animation: slideIn  0.28s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1) forwards; }
.screen-exit  { animation: slideOut 0.28s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1) forwards; }
```
Apply `.screen-enter` to the incoming screen and `.screen-exit` to the outgoing screen simultaneously in render().

### Tab switching — sliding panel, never a jump, never a full re-render
My Photos / With Me tabs and action tabs must slide content, not swap it abruptly.
Never call render() on a tab switch — it causes a full DOM rebuild which looks like a hard cut.
Instead, use a sliding wrapper:

```html
<!-- Tab panels sit side by side in a flex row -->
<div id="tab-wrapper" style="display:flex;width:200%;transition:transform 0.28s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1);will-change:transform;">
  <div style="width:50%;"><!-- My Photos content --></div>
  <div style="width:50%;"><!-- With Me content --></div>
</div>
```

```javascript
function setMainTab(t) {
  state.activeFilters.mainTab = t;
  const wrapper = document.getElementById('tab-wrapper');
  if (wrapper) wrapper.style.transform = t === 'my' ? 'translateX(0%)' : 'translateX(-50%)';
  // Update only the tab indicator underlines — no full re-render
  document.querySelectorAll('.main-tab-btn').forEach(btn => {
    const isActive = btn.dataset.tab === t;
    btn.style.fontWeight  = isActive ? '600' : '400';
    btn.style.color       = isActive ? T.text : T.textT;
    btn.style.borderBottom = isActive ? `2px solid ${T.blue}` : '2px solid transparent';
  });
}
```

### Bottom sheets — slide up from bottom
```css
.sheet-overlay { position:absolute;inset:0;background:rgba(0,0,0,.45);display:flex;align-items:flex-end; }
.sheet-card    { width:100%;background:#fff;border-radius:20px 20px 0 0;
                 transform:translateY(100%);transition:transform 0.28s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1);
                 will-change:transform; }
.sheet-card.open { transform:translateY(0); }
```
Open: add class `open` to `.sheet-card` on next frame after inserting into DOM.
Close: remove class `open`, then remove element after transition ends (280ms).

### Filter sub-chips row — slides down, not a jump
```css
.sub-chips-row { max-height:0; overflow:hidden; transition:max-height 0.2s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1); }
.sub-chips-row.open { max-height:48px; }
```

### Photo grid filter dimming — smooth opacity
```css
.photo-cell            { transition:opacity 0.25s ease; }
.photo-cell.dim        { opacity:0.15; }
```

### Face chip identification — colour transition
```css
.face-chip { transition:background 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease; }
```

### General rules
- `will-change:transform` only on elements that animate — do not apply globally
- No bounce, overshoot, or spring physics — calm and precise only
- No third-party animation libraries — zero dependencies
- All durations in milliseconds: screens/sheets 280ms, components 200ms, micro-interactions 150ms

